<plot>This entry in Columbia's "Cavalcade of Boradway" series has host Danton Walker taking the audience to 'The Embers' club, where progressive-jazz expert Joe Buhskin and His Sextette are performing. With Bushkin at the piano, the group opens with "Rat Race" and vocalist Dorothy Loudon lights a blues-torch with "The Devil and the Deep Blue Sea." Bushkin provides the finale playing and singing his own composition, "Oh, Look at Me Now."</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?097218</url></doc>
